<br>
The EULA prohibits you from "us[ing] any third party software to modify the Game to change Game play."  Does this change game play?  I don't really think so.  But Mythic clearly thinks that minimizing the game is a big deal.  I'll admit I didn't double-check the EULA before that post, and the language is more ambiguous than what I expected to find.  Based upon Mythic's statements in the past, however, they may well argue the point.<br>
<br>
My point was a practical one: you're talking about using a third-party program that enables you to do something (minimize the game, then resume play) that the game was specifically designed <i>not</i> to permit.  If you're looking to pick a fight with Mythic, that's probably a good way to do it.<br>
<br>
I have no problem with people minimizing the game.  Install the program and minimize away.  I just hope people consider the possible consequences and we don't see a bunch of "Ack, I got banned!" posts down the road.<br>
