<br>
Yes, using a third party program to actually hack the client and cause it to not terminate is a violation of the agreement, no question.<br>
<br>
But what if I create a DxWindows-type utility that modifies part of the OS to allow DAOC to run in a window?  I haven't touched the DAOC client at all, but rather am working between the DAOC client and the OS functions.  That is not a violation of the agreement, and I would like to see Mythic dare ban me over it.  <img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/biggrin.txt> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubobbinsrumblebelly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bobbins Rumblebelly</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://rcloues.home.mindspring.com/images/smiley.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/7/01 7:17:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alt-tab (background) functionality restored</span><hr size=1> Re: Point 1:<br>
<br>
Feh, that's a pretty sorry reason.  Today's computers are more than powerful enough to handle other programs in the background, especially if they're small programs like icq or winamp.  I regularly run Winamp in the background and have no trouble.  Together winamp and trillian use what, a total of 5 or 6 megs of memory? That's hardly about to cause any degredation in DAoC's performance, unless the computer is already way under spec...<br>
<br>
Re: Point 2:<br>
<br>
Active or not, we all pay the same fee, why does it matter how much stress we put on the system?  The cable tv company doesn't cut off my cable when I get up to grab a snack during a commercial break...<br>
<br>
Besides, claiming to not be disabling task switching by forcing the program to close if it loses focus is a pretty dubious claim.  The point of task switching is to be able to move uninterrupted between several different tasks.  Forcing a program to throw a tantrum and quit if task switching takes place is nothing more than a slightly less obvious way of disabling task switching.  <br>
<br>
Re: Point 3:<br>
<br>
When programs that allow people to alt-tab without closing DAoC become widespread, "casual" hacking will be just as common as it ever was.  Rewriting the code to detect such 'hacks' is a good thing, but imposing asinine limitations upon customers is not. <p><i>Need a new sig. Lawn gnomes stole the old one.</i></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessageRange?topicID=168.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessageRange?topicID=168.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessageRange?topicID=168.topic&start=61&stop=65>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessage?topicID=210.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessage?topicID=209.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.emailToFriend?topicID=168.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.threadControl?topicID=168.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=168.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=168.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BB